SIMPLE: epicycloidal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Epicycloidal
<hw>Ep`i*cy*cloid"al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Pertaining to
the epicycloid, or having its properties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Epicycloidal wheel</b></col>, <cd>a device for producing
straight-line motion from circular motion, on the principle that a pin
fastened in the periphery of a gear wheel will describe a straight line
when the wheel rolls around inside a fixed internal gear of twice its
diameter.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epideictic</ent>⟦br⟧
